title: PC-PTSD (IPC Session 1)
description: PC-PTSD form that is intended for IPC Session 1

item.text: A place to declare values that cannot be created using FHIRPath such as Coding. Retrieve the following items has answer value using variable expression, to use the declared value.
Observation ID of PC-PTSD Session 1 Score

Tip
The next five questions are from the Primary Care-PTSD Screen. These questions measure PTSD.

Example dialogue
"Now, I would like to ask you some questions to see if you have significant trauma in your life."
Sometimes things happen to people that are unusually or especially horrible, traumatic, or beyond the level of everyday stressors. Have you ever experienced this type of event?
I am going to list some of these events. Please tell me if you have experienced any of them before:

extension.valueString: Un accidente serio o un incendio
A serious accident or fire

valueCoding.display: A physical or sexual assault or abuse

extension.valueString: Abuso físico o sexual
A physical or sexual assault or abuse
Terremoto o inundación
An earthquake or flood
Guerra
A war

valueCoding.display: Seeing someone be killed or seriously injured

extension.valueString: Ver a alguien muerto o gravemente herido
Seeing someone be killed or seriously injured

valueCoding.display: Having a loved one die through homicide or suicide

extension.valueString: Tener un ser querido moror por asesinato o suicidio
Having a loved one die through homicide or suicide

item.text: In the past month, have you had nightmares about the event(s) or thought about the event(s) when you did not want to?

extension.valueString: En el mes pasado, ¿ha tenido pesadillas sobe este evento(s) o ha pensado en el evento(s) cuando no quería?
In the past month, have you had nightmares about the event(s) or thought about the event(s) when you did not want to?

item.text: In the past month, have you tried hard not to think about the event(s) or went out of your way to avoid situations that reminded you of the event(s)?

extension.valueString: En el mes pasado, ¿ha tratado de no pensar sobre este evento(s) o ha tratado de evitar situaciones que le recuerden este evento(s)?
In the past month, have you tried hard not to think about the event(s) or went out of your way to avoid situations that reminded you of the event(s)?

item.text: In the past month, have you been constantly on guard, watchful, or easily startled?

extension.valueString: En el mes pasado, ¿ha estado constantemente en guardia, vigilante o fácilmente asustado?
In the past month, have you been constantly on guard, watchful, or easily startled?

item.text: In the past month, have you felt numb or detached from people, activities, or your surroundings?

extension.valueString: En el mes pasado, ¿ha sentido desanimado o desprendido de personas, actividades, o su entorno?
In the past month, have you felt numb or detached from people, activities, or your surroundings?

item.text: In the past month, have you felt guilty or unable to stop blaming yourself or others for the events(s) or any problems the event(s) may have caused?

extension.valueString: En el mes pasado, ¿ha sentido culpable o que no pudo dejar de culpar a si mismo o a otra persona para el evento(s) o cualquier otro problema el evento(s) ha causado?
In the past month, have you felt guilty or unable to stop blaming yourself or others for the events(s) or any problems the event(s) may have caused?
Su puntaje PC-PTSD es
Your PC-PTSD score is

item.text:
Tip #1
List symptoms, describe severity (what the summed up scores mean), and impact on daily activities.

Tip #2
Please see severity levels for the PC-PTSD Screen:
• If the client scores a 3 or more, they may be experiencing PTSD.

Example dialogue
"Your score is an indication that the trauma you have is significantly impacting your life. This is something we may work on."
This score suggests that you may not be experiencing symptoms of PTSD
